<h1>Problem 1070 - 2022 ICMC, Round 2, P4 of 5, NC</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Fix a set of integers \(S\). An integer is <i>clean</i> if it is the sum of distinct elements of \(S\) in exactly one way, and <i>dirty</i> otherwise. Prove that the set of dirty numbers is either empty or infinite.<br><br>
<i>Note:</i> We consider the empty sum to equal \(0\).</p>
